=== Expected Outcomes and Implications

If HRV-guided pacing shows benefit:
    - Establishes HRV monitoring as standard of care adjunct
    - Provides objective tool for patients and clinicians
    - Informs development of HRV-based pacing apps and devices
    - Opens research direction for personalized pacing algorithms
If no benefit observed:
    - May indicate HRV is insufficiently predictive in ME/CFS
    - May suggest need for different HRV protocols or metrics
    - Would redirect research toward other objective pacing tools
